# Conventional Commits
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, missing semicolons, etc)
#   refactor - Code refactoring
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   ci       - CI/CD changes
#   build    - Build system changes
#   revert   - Revert previous commit
#
# Examples:
#   feat: add new contact form validation
#   fix(navbar): resolve mobile menu toggle issue
#   docs: update README with deployment instructions
#   style: format code with prettier
#   refactor: simplify component logic
#   test: add unit tests for utility functions
#   chore: update dependencies
#   perf: optimize image loading
#   ci: add GitHub Actions workflow
#   build: configure webpack optimization
#   revert: revert to previous stable version
#
# Scope is optional but recommended for clarity
# Description should be in present tense and concise 